            <fr:title text="Left ideal of a ring">Left ideal of a ring</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">MML <fr:link href="https://mizar.uwb.edu.pl/version/current/html/ideal_1.html#M1" type="external">ideal_1:def 1</fr:link></fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source">Dummit and Foote <fr:link href="/dummit-2004-abstract/" title="Abstract Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/dummit-2004-abstract/" display-uri="dummit-2004-abstract" type="local">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 7.3</fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source">Artin <fr:link href="/artin-2010-algebra/" title="Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/artin-2010-algebra/" display-uri="artin-2010-algebra" type="local">Algebra</fr:link> Section 11.3</fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source">Hungerford <fr:link href="/hungerford-1974-algebra/" title="Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/hungerford-1974-algebra/" display-uri="hungerford-1974-algebra" type="local">Algebra</fr:link> Section III.2</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/ring-0001/" title="Ring" uri="http://localhost:8000/ring-0001/" display-uri="ring-0001" type="local">Ring</fr:link>. A <html:dfn>Left Ideal</html:dfn> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> is a nonempty subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subseteq  R]]></fr:tex> such that
<html:ol><html:li>for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\in  R]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  I]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[rx\in  I]]></fr:tex>; and</html:li>
<html:li>for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  I]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x+y\in  I]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol></html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>We could speak of ideals in more general settings, e.g., rings without negation.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
