            <fr:title text="Ring morphism">Ring morphism</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Dummit and Foote <fr:link href="/dummit-2004-abstract/" title="Abstract Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/dummit-2004-abstract/" display-uri="dummit-2004-abstract" type="local">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 7.3</fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source">Artin <fr:link href="/artin-2010-algebra/" title="Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/artin-2010-algebra/" display-uri="artin-2010-algebra" type="local">Algebra</fr:link> Section 11.3</fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source">Hungerford <fr:link href="/hungerford-1974-algebra/" title="Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/hungerford-1974-algebra/" display-uri="hungerford-1974-algebra" type="local">Algebra</fr:link> Section III.1</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="/ring-0001/" title="Ring" uri="http://localhost:8000/ring-0001/" display-uri="ring-0001" type="local">Ring</fr:link>s. We define a <html:dfn>Ring Morphism</html:dfn> (or just a <html:dfn>Morphism</html:dfn> if unambiguous) to be a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi \colon  R\to  S]]></fr:tex> such that:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>Additive: for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  R]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi (x+y)=\varphi (x)+\varphi (y)]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li>Preserves zero: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi (0_{R})=0_{S}]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li>Multiplicative: for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  R]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi (xy)=\varphi (x)\varphi (y)]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li>Preserves one (when between unital rings): <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi (1_{R})=1_{S}]]></fr:tex> when there is a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{R}\in  R]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{S}\in  S]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
            <html:p><html:strong>Exercise:</html:strong> Do we really need <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi (0)=0]]></fr:tex> or is this a consequence of additivity?</html:p>
            <html:p><html:strong>Exercise:</html:strong> Do we really need <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi (1_{R})=1_{S}]]></fr:tex> or is this a consequence of the multiplicative property?</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
