            <fr:display-uri>gr-0017</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gr-0017/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Quaternion group isomorphic to subgroup of \GL _{2}(\CC )">Quaternion group isomorphic to subgroup of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\GL _{2}(\CC )]]></fr:tex></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>example</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Hungerford <fr:link href="/hungerford-1974-algebra/" title="Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/hungerford-1974-algebra/" display-uri="hungerford-1974-algebra" type="local">Algebra</fr:link> Exercise 1.2.3</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Consider the subgroup <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq \mathop {\textrm {GL}}\nolimits _{2}(\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> generated by powers and products of
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[A=\begin {pmatrix}0 & 1\\-1 & 0\end {pmatrix},\quad \hbox {and}\quad  B=\begin {pmatrix}0 & \mathrm {i}\\\mathrm {i} & 0\end {pmatrix}]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {i}^{2}=-1]]></fr:tex>. (We see <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A^{4}]]></fr:tex> is the identity matrix, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B^{4}]]></fr:tex> is the identity matrix.) Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to <fr:link href="/gr-0016/" title="Quaternion Group" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-0016/" display-uri="gr-0016" type="local">Quaternion Group</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Q_{8}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>The isomorphism is given by sending <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\mapsto  j]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\mapsto  k]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[AB\mapsto  i]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
